The Telegraph - Calcutta : Opinion
		 Wednesday, June 25, 2003 Subhas Chakraborty								Minister-in-charge, departments of transport and sports, government of West Bengal																																							The present set-up is inadequate to avert bank dacoities. The police need special training and must put in place an intelligence network. The banks also need to instal security gadgets like alarms. A good idea would be for all the banks in a locality to create a pool of resources. They should also pay for the costs the police have to bear to provide them security.
